## Understanding restatement (before any build)
The kit passed machines and failed the human. Three causes, three fixes plus one follow-up:
1. «Дал ключ, но ничего не произошло» → question 5 must CLOSE THE LOOP inside itself:
   token → «нажмите Start» → getUpdates poll (~60s honest) → chat_id captured = the head's
   H4 binding → the bot IMMEDIATELY says «я на связи; утром пришлю первый дайджест» →
   the r3-accepted head deployed (profile.conf + both plists + one healthy listener pass).
   Skip = zero effort, stated FIRST.
2. No journey map → first screen: «9 вопросов → ~3 минуты → в конце две строки»; headers «N из 9».
3. Finale abandoned → READY copy-paste block with the REAL workdir (`cd <workdir> && claude`,
   «скажите: qroky start») + VS Code line + honesty about claude's own first-run questions.
4. GATE-028 «да, спрашивать при установке» → question 9: machine-wide gesture opt-in,
   exactly two files under ~/.claude, idempotent, removable; I3 amended in the VENDORED skill.

## Design decisions (locked, each declared — not silent)
D1. Head gets ZERO edits. TG_HOME = <workdir>/.qroky/telegram/ — NOT inside framework/
    (state/log inside the vendored checkout would raise phantom «local changes» on every
    update; the F3 lesson). Wiring = profile.conf rendered there + two wrapper scripts
    (export QROKY_TG_HOME/QROKY_TG_ROOT, exec the head's own listener.sh/digest.sh
    unmodified) + two KIT-RENDERED plists pointing at the wrappers. The head's own
    install.sh is not called: its --bind is interactive (read -r) and its plists would
    home state inside framework/. Both plists ARE installed; the head's SCRIPTS run
    byte-identical. DECLARED LOUDLY here and in RESULT.md per INPUT §6.
D2. Binding = write state/chat_id (tmp+mv) — the exact file the head's bound_chat_id()
    reads: this IS the head's H4 binding, done non-interactively by the installer.
    Offset handoff: the consumed /start update_id is written to state/offset so the
    listener's first pass does NOT re-process the owner's Start press.
D3. Today's digest-sent-<date> marker is pre-written before the health-check pass:
    the listener's M4 safety net would otherwise fire a digest AT INSTALL TIME whenever
    the install happens after 09:05 — contradicting the hello's own promise «утром
    пришлю первый дайджест». First digest genuinely arrives next morning.
D4. Timeout / Start never pressed → token stays stored, head NOT deployed (stricter S6
    reading of INPUT §1: a bound-to-nobody listener polling every 30s is a half-alive
    state the founder cannot see). One command completes everything later:
    bash install.sh --enable-telegram (mirrors --enable-heartbeat, as INPUT asks).
D5. The installer speaks Bot API directly via curl for getMe/getUpdates/sendMessage —
    lib.sh is NOT sourced into install.sh (both define log(); a source would silently
    shadow one of them). Token handling identical to v0.1.x: file mode 600, masked
    everywhere, negative grep stays the harness gate.
D6. chat_id parse: sed/grep over the Bot API's machine-generated compact JSON
    ("chat":{"id":N) — keeps the kit's H1 dependency contract (bash+POSIX+curl+git,
    no python requirement in the interview path). The head keeps its python parser.
D7. New sandbox-only test hook QROKY_TEST_START_WAIT (seconds; default 60 in
    production, unset = 60) so the no-Start timeout scenario need not wait a real
    minute. Same class as QROKY_TEST_DELAY_*; declared in install.sh's header.
D8. Machine-wide markers: <!-- qroky-machinewide:start/end --> in ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md
    (created if absent); skill copy cmp -s guarded. ONLY these two paths ever touch ~.
    Removal = delete the block between markers + delete the skill file; documented in
    READMEs and in the installer's own confirmation line.

## Harness-checklist (INFO-025) — 9 answers for the v0.2 additions
1. Failure modes named? — Start never pressed (timeout, honest skip); head absent from
   older vendored rulebook (degrade + enable-later); sendMessage hello fails (retry
   ladder then honest line — binding kept, deploy continues); launchctl bootstrap fails
   (ladder + degrade, install continues); ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md unwritable (loud fail of
   Q9 only, install continues project-only).
2. Resume/kill safety? — same state machine: step_telegram/step_machinewide commit
   'done' only after their work; kill mid-step re-asks that step only (scenario 2 keeps
   proving it with the delay hook).
3. Failure ladder? — every new remedy-able action (getUpdates poll, sendMessage,
   bootstrap) runs ≤2 auto-retries then a concrete human line; the Start-wait itself is
   a TIMED HONEST WAIT, not a retry loop (waiting longer is not a remedy — a human line
   with the enable-later command is).
4. Logs self-contained? — every new log line carries step + outcome; token only masked.
5. Secrets? — token file remains the ONE sanctioned place; hello/getUpdates URLs never
   logged raw (curl stderr captured + masked, same as validation); negative grep over
   state/log/telemetry/git extended to the new flow's transcripts.
6. Idempotency? — Q9 marker-guarded + cmp; telegram deploy check→do (profile.conf/
   wrappers/plists rewritten only when differing; binding never overwritten silently);
   healthy rerun stays a zero-write health check (scenario 3 diff proves it).
7. Question inventory? — EXACTLY NINE: tags IV-POINT:1..9, hardened count assert
   updated (point 9 present, max = 9, never 10+).
8. Real-data perimeter? — harness runs in mktemp sandboxes with fake HOME; the two
   ~-writes are exercised ONLY against fake HOMEs; nothing sent to real Telegram (stub).
9. Human hand-off points? — Start press (physical phone action, can't be automated —
   honest wait + skip); claude's own first-run questions (finale says so honestly);
   BotFather creation (unchanged walkthrough).

